summary: So Arya is almost always standing like the first image for the past couple of seasons because it’s her power stance. She fears...
body: So Arya is almost always standing like the first image for the past couple of seasons because it’s her power stance. She fears no one and feels confident. However, you’ll note how much her body language differed when she left Gendry in the forge. She went from her usual power stances, typically hands behind her back or hand on a weapon, to walking backwards with her arms in a fig leaf position, hands clasped over her abdomen. She’s feeling comfortable, vulnerable, and kind of goofy. To sum up, Gendry got her fucked up.
